#. <section class="sutta" id="an6.25"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.25:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.25:0.2"
msgid "3. Anuttariyavagga"
msgstr "3. Unsurpassable"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.25:0.3"
msgid "25. Anussatiṭṭhānasutta"
msgstr "25. Topics for Recollection"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an6.25:1.1"
msgid "“Chayimāni, bhikkhave, anussatiṭṭhānāni."
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these six topics for recollection."

msgctxt "an6.25:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni cha?"
msgstr "What six?"

msgctxt "an6.25:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako tathāgataṃ anussarati:"
msgstr "Firstly, a noble disciple recollects the Realized One:"

msgctxt "an6.25:1.4"
msgid "‘itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in "
"knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those "
"who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’"

msgctxt "an6.25:1.5"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye ariyasāvako tathāgataṃ anussarati, nevassa tasmiṃ "
"samaye rāgapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti, na dosapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti, na "
"mohapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti;"
msgstr ""
"When a noble disciple recollects the Realized One their mind is not full of "
"greed, hate, and delusion."

msgctxt "an6.25:1.6"
msgid ""
"ujugatamevassa tasmiṃ samaye cittaṃ hoti, nikkhantaṃ muttaṃ vuṭṭhitaṃ "
"gedhamhā."
msgstr ""
"At that time their mind is unswerving. They’ve left behind greed; they’re "
"free of it and have risen above it."

msgctxt "an6.25:1.7"
msgid "‘Gedho’ti kho, bhikkhave, pañcannetaṃ kāmaguṇānaṃ adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr "‘Greed’ is a term for the five kinds of sensual stimulation."

msgctxt "an6.25:1.8"
msgid ""
"Idampi kho, bhikkhave, ārammaṇaṃ karitvā evam’idhekacce sattā visujjhanti. "
"(1)"
msgstr "Relying on this some sentient beings are purified."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an6.25:2.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako dhammaṃ anussarati:"
msgstr "Furthermore, a noble disciple recollects the teaching:"

msgctxt "an6.25:2.2"
msgid "‘svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo … pe … paccattaṃ veditabbo viññūhī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The teaching is well explained by the Buddha—realizable in this very life, "
"immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible "
"people can know it for themselves.’"

msgctxt "an6.25:2.3"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye ariyasāvako dhammaṃ anussarati, nevassa tasmiṃ "
"samaye rāgapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti, na dosapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti, na "
"mohapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti;"
msgstr ""
"When a noble disciple recollects the teaching their mind is not full of "
"greed, hate, and delusion. …"

msgctxt "an6.25:2.4"
msgid ""
"ujugatamevassa tasmiṃ samaye cittaṃ hoti, nikkhantaṃ muttaṃ vuṭṭhitaṃ "
"gedhamhā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.25:2.5"
msgid "‘Gedho’ti kho, bhikkhave, pañcannetaṃ kāmaguṇānaṃ adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.25:2.6"
msgid ""
"Idampi kho, bhikkhave, ārammaṇaṃ karitvā evam’idhekacce sattā visujjhanti. "
"(2)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.313"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an6.25:3.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako saṅghaṃ anussarati:"
msgstr "Furthermore, a noble disciple recollects the Saṅgha:"

msgctxt "an6.25:3.2"
msgid ""
"‘suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho … pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ "
"lokassā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The Saṅgha of the Buddha’s disciples is practicing the way that’s good, "
"straightforward, methodical, and proper. It consists of the four pairs, the "
"eight individuals. This is the Saṅgha of the Buddha’s disciples that is "
"worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of "
"a teacher’s offering, worthy of greeting with joined palms, and is the "
"supreme field of merit for the world.’"

msgctxt "an6.25:3.3"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye ariyasāvako saṅghaṃ anussarati, nevassa tasmiṃ "
"samaye rāgapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti, na dosapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti, na "
"mohapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti;"
msgstr ""
"When a noble disciple recollects the Saṅgha their mind is not full of greed, "
"hate, and delusion. …"

msgctxt "an6.25:3.4"
msgid ""
"ujugatamevassa tasmiṃ samaye cittaṃ hoti, nikkhantaṃ muttaṃ vuṭṭhitaṃ "
"gedhamhā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.25:3.5"
msgid "‘Gedho’ti kho, bhikkhave, pañcannetaṃ kāmaguṇānaṃ adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.25:3.6"
msgid ""
"Idampi kho, bhikkhave, ārammaṇaṃ karitvā evam’idhekacce sattā visujjhanti. "
"(3)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an6.25:4.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako attano sīlāni anussarati akhaṇḍāni … pe "
"… samādhisaṃvattanikāni."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a noble disciple recollects their own ethical precepts, which "
"are unbroken, impeccable, spotless, and unmarred, liberating, praised by "
"sensible people, not mistaken, and leading to immersion."

msgctxt "an6.25:4.2"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye ariyasāvako sīlaṃ anussarati, nevassa tasmiṃ "
"samaye rāgapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti, na dosapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti, na "
"mohapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti;"
msgstr ""
"When a noble disciple recollects their ethical precepts their mind is not "
"full of greed, hate, and delusion. …"

msgctxt "an6.25:4.3"
msgid ""
"ujugatamevassa tasmiṃ samaye cittaṃ hoti, nikkhantaṃ muttaṃ vuṭṭhitaṃ "
"gedhamhā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.25:4.4"
msgid "‘Gedho’ti kho, bhikkhave, pañcannetaṃ kāmaguṇānaṃ adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.25:4.5"
msgid ""
"Idampi kho, bhikkhave, ārammaṇaṃ karitvā evam’idhekacce sattā visujjhanti. "
"(4)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an6.25:5.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako attano cāgaṃ anussarati:"
msgstr "Furthermore, a noble disciple recollects their own generosity:"

msgctxt "an6.25:5.2"
msgid "‘lābhā vata me. Suladdhaṃ vata me … pe …"
msgstr "‘I’m so fortunate, so very fortunate!"

msgctxt "an6.25:5.3"
msgid "yācayogo dānasaṃvibhāgarato’ti."
msgstr ""
"Among people full of the stain of stinginess I live at home rid of the stain "
"of stinginess, freely generous, open-handed, loving to let go, committed to "
"charity, loving to give and to share.’"

msgctxt "an6.25:5.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr ""
"When a noble disciple recollects their generosity their mind is not full of "
"greed, hate, and delusion. …"

msgctxt "an6.25:5.5"
msgid "Evam’idhekacce sattā visujjhanti. (5)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.314"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an6.25:6.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako devatā anussarati:"
msgstr "Furthermore, a noble disciple recollects the deities:"

msgctxt "an6.25:6.2"
msgid ""
"‘santi devā cātumahārājikā, santi devā tāvatiṃsā, santi devā yāmā, santi "
"devā tusitā, santi devā nimmānaratino, santi devā paranimmitavasavattino, "
"santi devā brahmakāyikā, santi devā tatuttari."
msgstr ""
"‘There are the Gods of the Four Great Kings, the Gods of the Thirty-Three, "
"the Gods of Yama, the Joyful Gods, the Gods Who Love to Create, the Gods Who "
"Control the Creations of Others, the Gods of Brahmā’s Group, and gods even "
"higher than these."

msgctxt "an6.25:6.3"
msgid "Yathārūpāya saddhāya samannāgatā tā devatā ito cutā tattha upapannā;"
msgstr ""
"When those deities passed away from here, they were reborn there because of "
"their faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and wisdom."

msgctxt "an6.25:6.4"
msgid ""
"mayhampi tathārūpā saddhā saṃvijjati. Yathārūpena sīlena … sutena … cāgena … "
"paññāya samannāgatā tā devatā ito cutā tattha upapannā; mayhampi tathārūpā "
"paññā saṃvijjatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"I, too, have the same kind of faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and "
"wisdom.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an6.25:7.1"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye ariyasāvako attano ca tāsañca devatānaṃ saddhañca "
"sīlañca sutañca cāgañca paññañca anussarati nevassa tasmiṃ samaye "
"rāgapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti, na dosapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti, na "
"mohapariyuṭṭhitaṃ cittaṃ hoti;"
msgstr ""
"When a noble disciple recollects the faith, ethics, learning, generosity, "
"and wisdom of both themselves and the deities their mind is not full of "
"greed, hate, and delusion."

msgctxt "an6.25:7.2"
msgid ""
"ujugatamevassa tasmiṃ samaye cittaṃ hoti, nikkhantaṃ muttaṃ vuṭṭhitaṃ "
"gedhamhā."
msgstr ""
"At that time their mind is unswerving. They’ve left behind greed; they’re "
"free of it and have risen above it."

msgctxt "an6.25:7.3"
msgid "‘Gedho’ti kho, bhikkhave, pañcannetaṃ kāmaguṇānaṃ adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr "‘Greed’ is a term for the five kinds of sensual stimulation."

msgctxt "an6.25:7.4"
msgid ""
"Idampi kho, bhikkhave, ārammaṇaṃ karitvā evam’idhekacce sattā visujjhanti. "
"(6)"
msgstr "Relying on this some sentient beings are purified."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an6.25:8.1"
msgid "Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cha anussatiṭṭhānānī”ti."
msgstr "These are the six topics for recollection.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.25:8.2"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
